<br>
For some, it is the risk vs. the reward that is the real excitement, knowing that you MIGHT just lose a precious items (that is not No-Drop) to someone if you lose a fight.  While both Vallon Zek and Tallon Zek were set-up that way, they were then changed to coin-only loot, and it does have a bit less excitement since you know you won't be losing any items.<br>
But that also means you are able to wear your best equipment while fighting, not having the dilemma of naked casters who risk nothing (other than death) as they take your Ravenscale BP or Gold Diamond Mask.<br>
<br>
Personally, I would say try out either Vallon Zek or Tallon Zek and level up a character to about 9th or 10th level, and then go out and have fun with PvP.  Mind you, the areas you used to be able to go to will be quite different as you will see that the various teams will take over regions for leveling up or camping for items.  If you find that either of the Team servers does not seem as quite exciting as you would like, try Rallos Zek.<br>
<br>
For myself, I prefer the concept of teams where you have allies you know you can depend on, versus Rallos Zek where anyone within the level restrictions can backstab you if they feel like it.  Of course, we are still dealing with x-teamers, but hopefully that will be fixed.<br>
